description:
Hmm... Since Yelp is all about "word of mouth," I figure the best review I can write is what I told my dinner companion when he asked me what I thought about the meal:

"Meh. I would say 3 stars, at best. I thought the place was super cute... small, cozy, authentic-looking (it totally reminded me of the yummy hole-in-the-wall spots in Japan). But the sushi was mediocre. In a blind taste test I probably would knock it down to 2 stars."

So there it is, my immediate response to Sushi Time. Maybe it was an off night, it's 4 1/2 star rating from 200 yelpers seems quite confusing to me

Awesome - the atmosphere and that they let you pick out your own sake glass from a box of glasses (fun!), the mish-mash of table settings, the kitschy Japanese mobiles; 

Mediocre - the barbie roll (there's one kind of like this at Tokyo GoGo that's BOMB), the sashimi, the seaweed salad;

Not awesome - the speed racer roll.
